#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn48.40"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.40:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.40:0.2"
msgid "4. Sukhindriyavagga "
msgstr "4. The Pleasure Faculty "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 40. Uppaṭipāṭikasutta → uppatika (pts1)
msgctxt "sn48.40:0.3"
msgid "40. Uppaṭipāṭikasutta "
msgstr "40. Irregular Order "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn48.40:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, indriyāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five faculties. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.3"
msgid "Dukkhindriyaṃ, domanassindriyaṃ, sukhindriyaṃ, somanassindriyaṃ, upekkhindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "The faculties of pain, sadness, pleasure, happiness, and equanimity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.40:1.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato uppajjati dukkhindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "While a mendicant is meditating—diligent, keen, and resolute—the faculty of pain arises. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.5"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

# NOTE: Compare AN 2.77-81.
msgctxt "sn48.40:1.6"
msgid "‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ, tañca kho sanimittaṃ sanidānaṃ sasaṅkhāraṃ sappaccayaṃ. "
msgstr "‘The faculty of pain has arisen in me. And that has a foundation, a source, a condition, and a reason. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.7"
msgid "Tañca animittaṃ anidānaṃ asaṅkhāraṃ appaccayaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ uppajjissatī’ti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "It’s not possible for the faculty of pain to arise without a foundation, a source, a condition, or a reason.’ "

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.8"
msgid "So dukkhindriyañca pajānāti, dukkhindriyasamudayañca pajānāti, dukkhindriyanirodhañca pajānāti, yattha cuppannaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati tañca pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand the faculty of pain, its origin, its cessation, and where that faculty of pain that’s arisen ceases without anything left over. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.9"
msgid "Kattha cuppannaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati? "
msgstr "And where does that faculty of pain that’s arisen cease without anything left over? "

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.10"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.11"
msgid "ettha cuppannaṃ dukkhindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati. "
msgstr "That’s where the faculty of pain that’s arisen ceases without anything left over. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:1.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu aññāsi dukkhindriyassa nirodhaṃ, tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati’. "
msgstr "They’re called a mendicant who understands the cessation of the faculty of pain, and who applies their mind to that end. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.214, sc2
msgctxt "sn48.40:2.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato uppajjati domanassindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "While a mendicant is meditating—diligent, keen, and resolute—the faculty of sadness arises. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:2.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "sn48.40:2.3"
msgid "‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ domanassindriyaṃ, tañca kho sanimittaṃ sanidānaṃ sasaṅkhāraṃ sappaccayaṃ. "
msgstr "‘The faculty of sadness has arisen in me. And that has a foundation, a source, a condition, and a reason. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:2.4"
msgid "tañca animittaṃ anidānaṃ asaṅkhāraṃ appaccayaṃ domanassindriyaṃ uppajjissatī’ti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "It’s not possible for the faculty of sadness to arise without a foundation, a source, a condition, or a reason.’ "

msgctxt "sn48.40:2.5"
msgid "So domanassindriyañca pajānāti, domanassindriyasamudayañca pajānāti, domanassindriyanirodhañca pajānāti, yattha cuppannaṃ domanassindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati tañca pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand the faculty of sadness, its origin, its cessation, and where that faculty of sadness that’s arisen ceases without anything left over. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:2.6"
msgid "Kattha cuppannaṃ domanassindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati? "
msgstr "And where does that faculty of sadness that’s arisen cease without anything left over? "

msgctxt "sn48.40:2.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, "
msgstr "It’s when, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:2.8"
msgid "ettha cuppannaṃ domanassindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati. "
msgstr "That’s where the faculty of sadness that’s arisen ceases without anything left over. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:2.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu aññāsi domanassindriyassa nirodhaṃ, tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati’. "
msgstr "They’re called a mendicant who understands the cessation of the faculty of sadness, and who applies their mind to that end. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn48.40:3.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato uppajjati sukhindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "While a mendicant is meditating—diligent, keen, and resolute—the faculty of pleasure arises. "

