msgid "tañca animittaṃ anidānaṃ asaṅkhāraṃ appaccayaṃ sukhindriyaṃ uppajjissatī’ti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "it’s not possible for the faculty of pleasure to arise without a foundation, a source, a condition, or a reason.’ "

msgctxt "sn48.40:3.5"
msgid "So sukhindriyañca pajānāti, sukhindriyasamudayañca pajānāti, sukhindriyanirodhañca pajānāti, yattha cuppannaṃ sukhindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati tañca pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand the faculty of pleasure, its origin, its cessation, and where that faculty of pleasure that’s arisen ceases without anything left over. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:3.6"
msgid "Kattha cuppannaṃ sukhindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati? "
msgstr "And where does that faculty of pleasure that’s arisen cease without anything left over? "

msgctxt "sn48.40:3.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, "
msgstr "It’s when, with the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’ "

msgctxt "sn48.40:3.8"
msgid "ettha cuppannaṃ sukhindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati. "
msgstr "That’s where the faculty of pleasure that’s arisen ceases without anything left over. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:3.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu aññāsi sukhindriyassa nirodhaṃ, tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati’. "
msgstr "They’re called a mendicant who understands the cessation of the faculty of pleasure, and who applies their mind to that end. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.215, sc4
msgctxt "sn48.40:4.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato uppajjati somanassindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "While a mendicant is meditating—diligent, keen, and resolute—the faculty of happiness arises. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:4.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "sn48.40:4.3"
msgid "‘uppannaṃ kho me idaṃ somanassindriyaṃ, tañca kho sanimittaṃ sanidānaṃ sasaṅkhāraṃ sappaccayaṃ. "
msgstr "‘The faculty of happiness has arisen in me. And that has a foundation, a source, a condition, and a reason. "

