msgid "tañca animittaṃ anidānaṃ asaṅkhāraṃ appaccayaṃ somanassindriyaṃ uppajjissatī’ti—netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "it’s not possible for the faculty of happiness to arise without a foundation, a source, a condition, or a reason.’ "

msgctxt "sn48.40:4.5"
msgid "So somanassindriyañca pajānāti, somanassindriyasamudayañca pajānāti, somanassindriyanirodhañca pajānāti, yattha cuppannaṃ somanassindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati tañca pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand the faculty of happiness, its origin, its cessation, and where that faculty of happiness that’s arisen ceases without anything left over. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:4.6"
msgid "Kattha cuppannaṃ somanassindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati? "
msgstr "And where does that faculty of happiness that’s arisen cease without anything left over? "

msgctxt "sn48.40:4.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, "
msgstr "It’s when, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:4.8"
msgid "ettha cuppannaṃ somanassindriyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati. "
msgstr "That’s where the faculty of happiness that’s arisen ceases without anything left over. "

msgctxt "sn48.40:4.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu aññāsi somanassindriyassa nirodhaṃ, tadatthāya cittaṃ upasaṃharati’. "
msgstr "They’re called a mendicant who understands the cessation of the faculty of happiness, and who applies their mind to that end. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.216, sc5
msgctxt "sn48.40:5.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato uppajjati upekkhindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "While a mendicant is meditating—diligent, keen, and resolute—the faculty of equanimity arises. "

